                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20 Missions/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-06T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 6, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 6—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>317. Department’s 243, April 21. Prime Minister, who has been ill for some time,
                    has now advised me informally that he personally is agreeable to extension of
                    Schwarzkopf contract but will investigate matter and furnish Legation with an
                    official opinion in the near future. Saed states he has been impressed by
                    Schwarzkopf’s eagerness and industry and would like to see him remain in Iran
                    although, he states, no manifest results of his efforts have been visible to
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
